    <h2 class="header__medium">Getting Started</h2>
    <div class="content-block">
      To get started with <span class="important">particleLib</span> just follow these few steps.
    </div>

    <h2 class="header__medium">Instructions: </h2>

    <div class="content-block__small ">
      <span class="important">Install</span>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block code-block">
      <code>npm install particle_library</code>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block attention">
    Once installed, it will work in amd and commonjs enviroments.
    </div>

    <div class="content-block__small">
      <span class="important">Require</span>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block code-block">
      <code>
        const p = require("particle_library");<br/>
        <br/>
        const vec = new p.Vector();<br/>
        const particle = new p.Particle();<br/>
        const utils = p.Utils();<br/>
      </code>
    </div>
    
    <div class="content-block__small">
      <span class="important">Setup</span>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block__small">
        Create a canvas with html.
    </div>

    <div class="content-block code-block" style="padding-left: -10px;">
      <code>
        &lt;html&gt;<br/>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;head&gt;<br/>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;script src="./particleLib.js"&gt;<br/>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/head&gt;<br/>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;body&gt;<br/>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;canvas id="space"&gt;&lt;/canvas&gt;<br/>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/body&gt;<br/>
        &lt;/html&gt;
      </code>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block__small">
      <span class="important">Use</span>
    </div>
    
    <div class="content-block__small">
        Make sure the paticleLib is avaiable in your context. It is globally available here. Using the vector class we can create random vectors on the screen and start drawing.
    </div>

    <div class="content-block code-block">
      <code>
        &lt;script&gt;</br>
        const p = particleLib;<br/>
        const vec = new p.Vector();<br/>
        const canvas = document.getElementById("space");<br/>
        const context = canvas.getContext("2d");<br/>
        <br/>
        (function animate() {<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;const myVec = vec.random(0, 100);<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;ctx.beginPath();<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;ctx.moveTo(myVec.get("x"), myVec.get("x");<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;ctx.lineTo(myVec.get("y"), myVec.get("y");<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;ctx.stroke();<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;window.requestAnimationFrame(animate);<br/>
        });<br/>
        &lt;/script&gt;
      </code>
